  "text": "According to a study conducted in the United Kingdom, women living in sociallydeprived areas also had a limited knowledge of cervical cancer risks and prevention strategies [CITATION_1] . Researchers of a similar study in South Africa, where cervical cancer is also the second-leading cause of death among women, stated prevention methods and materials are necessary to inform women about HPv, cervical cancer, screening and discussing the topic with children [CITATION_2] .",
